## Steps

### step 1
id: navigate-to-payments-denials
instruction: Click "Payments & Denials" in the main sidebar under "My Workspace."
success_criteria: You are on the Payments & Denials page. You can see Deposits, Remittances, and Denials tabs, and an "Upload ERA" button in the top-right.
anchor: "Payments & Denials"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The "Payments & Denials" link is in the left sidebar.

### step 2
id: click-upload-era
instruction: Click the "Upload ERA" button in the top-right corner.
success_criteria: An upload dialog has opened asking you to select a billing account and upload an ERA file.
anchor: "Upload ERA"
on_success: next
on_stuck: The button is at the top right of the page.

### step 3
id: select-account-and-file
instruction: Select the billing account (NPI) the ERA belongs to, then drag and drop your ERA file into the upload area or click to browse. Accepted formats: .835, .era, .edi, .pdf.
success_criteria: The file appears in the upload zone with its filename. The "Process ERA File" button is active.
anchor: "Process ERA File"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click the drop zone to browse for the file. ERA files come from your payer via portal, email, or SFTP.

### step 4
id: process-era
instruction: Click "Process ERA File" to upload and process the remittance.
success_criteria: The dialog closes. For EDI files, processing is instant. For PDFs, a "Processing..." message appears and you'll get a notification when done. Deposits, Remittances, and Denials tabs update with the new payment data.
anchor: "Process ERA File"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Click the button. The system processes the ERA and populates payment data automatically.

## Completion Message
era uploaded! altair is matching each payment to your claims and identifying any denials. check the Deposits tab for the payment summary and the Denials tab for any denied claims.

